:["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Conyers","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire, of Norman origin): habitational name from either of two places in northern France, Coignières in Seine-et-Oise or Cogners in Sarthe. Alternatively, a variant of   Conyer  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Conyer","meanings":["English: occupational name for a minter, a coiner of money, from an agent derivative of Old French <i>coignier</i> ‘to stamp money, to mint’."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert de Conyers was born in 1130, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Robert de Conyers I. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1130–":"1130–Surnud","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1165–1238":"1165–1238","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","about 1150":"umbes 1150","1238":"1238","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","Sockburn, Durham, England":"Sockburn, Durham, England","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Galfred, Yorkshire, England":"Clifford, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1130–":"1130–Kuollut","1130–Male":"1130–Kuollut","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1165–1238":"1165–1238","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","about 1150":"noin 1150","1238":"1238","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","Sockburn, Durham, England":"Sockburn, Durham, England","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Galfred, Yorkshire, England":"Clifford, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1130–":"1130–Décédée","1130–Male":"1130–Décédé","1150–Male":"1150–Décédé","1165–1238":"1165–1238","1130–Female":"1130–Décédée","about 1150":"environ 1150","1238":"1238","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","Sockburn, Durham, England":"Sockburn, Durham, Angleterre","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Galfred, Yorkshire, England":"Clifford, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert de Conyers est née en 1130, à Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils avec Robert de Conyers I. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1130–":"1130–Verstorben","1130–Male":"1130–Verstorben","1150–Male":"1150–Verstorben","1165–1238":"1165–1238","1130–Female":"1130–Verstorben","about 1150":"um 1150","1238":"1238","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","Sockburn, Durham, England":"Sockburn, Durham, England","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Galfred, Yorkshire, England":"Clifford, Yorksh